name: Ken Harbaugh
tweet: There's so much more to say, but here's the thing: my opponent? We don't know where he stands. @RepBobGibbs has been in Congress for 8 years and has never introduced a bill that's been signed into law. He won't even debate me or hold a public event. It's time for a change.

name: Ken Harbaugh
tweet: And I mentioned healthcare before, but let's get a little more specific: Let's bring down drug costs with more competitive bidding. Let's protect Medicare and social security from the cuts Washington politicians have proposed. There's so much to be done, and DC's doing squat.

name: Ken Harbaugh
tweet: And while we're talking education, we need to talk about schools. Schools were shut down this month b/c of no AC! It's unacceptable and too common - 50% of school districts have deteriorating buildings. When we fund infrastructure, let's include schools in the process

name: Ken Harbaugh
tweet: And we also need to take care of our veterans. We owe a debt to all those who fought for our country - and their families. Let's make sure they get world-class healthcare. And let's make sure mental health services are fully funded and they have access to education and retraining

name: Ken Harbaugh
tweet: But we can't stop there: we need to address the opioid epidemic for what it is - an epidemic. Our current rep let a hospital close down in our district in the midst of this disaster. We need people to fight for all our residents and get the requisite funding to match

name: Ken Harbaugh
tweet: So glad you’re asking! Too many policies for a tweet, but here’s a start: we need to make healthcare affordable, bring good-paying jobs back to OH, and elect folks who put country over party.
